# TDD Guide Rule

When the task is in implementation and requires test-first execution, use the shared TDD protocol before writing or extending production code.

Follow:

- `AGENTS.md`
- `.agents/skills/tdd-guide/SKILL.md`

TDD requirements:

- define one clear behavior at a time
- write the failing test first
- verify it fails for the expected reason
- write only the minimal implementation needed to pass
- refactor only after tests are green
- keep bug-fix tests as regression protection

Do not treat this as a language-specific testing guide. Its job is to enforce test-first execution and constrain implementation order.
